http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Founder%E2%80%99s-Day-fete-at-Arya-Vaidya-Sala/article14006761.ece

: Kottakkal Arya Vaidya Sala will celebrate its Founder’s Day with a variety of programmes on January 30. Lyricist Sreekumaran Thampi will inaugurate the celebrations.Writer N.S. Madhavan will preside over the function, to be held in the courtyard of Kailasa Mandiram, Kottakkal.Insurance Ombudsman P.K. Vijayakumar will deliver the P.S. Varier Memorial Lecture.He will speak on the importance of insurance in modern life. Khadeeja Mumtaz, environmental activist and former faculty member of the Government Medical College, Kozhikode, will make the commemorative speech.Arya Vaidya Sala Managing Trustee P.K. Warrier will give away Arya Vaidya Sala’s annual awards to Ayurveda students.Five awards, including the Centenary Award of 2015, will be distributed on the occasion.Arya Vaidya Sala employees and their family will present a variety entertainment programme in the afternoon. Akshara Jwala, Ambalapuzha, will present a drama titled Mumpe Parakkunna Pakshikal .